post_text:
PROM HAS BEEN CANCELLED

Hello W-K Families,

As you know, we had July 17 reserved for Prom. As that date has become closer, we needed to make a decision.

We will need to cancel Prom.

We are saddened to do this, but the MN Department of Education and MN Department of Health mandates have not lifted enough to allow for an event like this. We know this is disappointing news, and we wish that we could continue the tradition. We are hopeful that we will be able to offer Prom in 2021. If any members of the class of 2020 would like to attend at that time, they are welcome.

As always, if you have any questions, please reach out to Stacy Schultz at sschultz@wkfalcons.org or call 651-565-3559 ext. 250. Take care and stay safe.

UPDATE:
To WK families that qualified for free or reduced meals during the 2019-2020 school year:

The P-EBT (Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer) program has been extended through July 31!
-If you missed the June 30 deadline to apply, you may still apply until July 31. You could receive up to $325 per month per child, retroactive to the time of distance learning last spring.
-If you already applied and received benefits, or if you received benefits without applying because you already had a SNAP card, you will automatically receive an additional $50/month for July and August.
-Applications must be completed online at www.mn.p-ebt.org.
-If you have questions, you can call 800-657-3698 or 651-431-4050.

Hope to see a lot of you during our senior celebration parade!

May 19 Parade Routes:
Starts in Kellogg: Students will line up at 6:15 pm behind St. Agnes Catholic Church on W. Glasgow Ave. The parade will begin at 6:30 pm. The route will start on S. 1st Street and E. Belvidere Ave, head east to S. Dodge St and take a left, then take another left on W. Winona Ave.

Wabasha Route: (Homecoming route):
At 7:00 pm, coming from W-K High School, north on Hiawatha Dr. E, turning right on Broadway Ave, Left on 3rd St. E., right on Pembrooke Ave, Left of Main St. and a left on Bridge Ave.

Today would have been the opening night of BIG FiSH THE MUSICAL at W-K. Due to Covid-19 we have been unable to produce this show. My goal is to produce it this summer before school starts again. In honor of the students who worked on the show, with their help, I have created a video preview of the show for you to watch. It features some students singing their songs from the show remotely, some zoom rehearsal clips, and video clips of our choreography rehearsals at the start of March. The video is an hour and 10 minutes. Please take time today to watch and support the Waballogg Performers. We hope we can perform the production live on stage soon. Tonight at 7 p.m. please stop and take a moment to think about us. In the meantime, please enjoy the talent of our students. Look for future announcements of when we will actually perform the show.

Monday, May 4th
8:30 AM - 9:00 AM
W-K Main Parking Lot

Staff will line the sidewalk of the main parking lot keeping proper social distance. Staff will be holding signs of encouragement, positivity and gratefulness.

Parents and students will enter the main parking lot and drive around the main parking lot. We will direct all cars leaving the parking lot during this time to turn right and go toward Wabasha. We know this may be inconvenient, but it will make it safer as we are hoping for and planning for a big turnout.

This event is a chance for us to see each other and say hi AND also say thanks for what we have all done during the COVID-19 pandemic while still being safe.

Staff will stay on the sidewalk and parade participants will need to stay in their vehicles.

Please be careful entering and exiting the parking lot.
We hope to see you even if for just a bit on Monday as we are so excited to see you!

W-K Virtual Spirit Week

Join us in celebrating our Falcon Pride by participating in our virtual spirit week
Monday, April 27th to Friday, May 1st. Have fun with it and be sure to send your photos to yearbook@wkfalcons.org.
• Monday, April 27th: Summertime Vibes/Shades Day-Wear your summer styles, sunhat, shades, flip flops, and don't forget your sunscreen!
• Tuesday, April 28th: Hazmat/COVID Day or Crazy Hair/Hat Day- Show us your best protective gear to fight the spread of germs OR show off a fun hat or those crazy hair styles.
• Wednesday, April 29th: Best Dressed-Dress to the 9's. Get out that dress, fancy shirt, blazer, do your hair, and show us the celebrities have nothing on you (could even put on a prom dress/tux).
• Thursday, April 30th: Virtual Twin Day-Plan it out with someone and send in a pic of YOU and whomever you are virtually twinning with. If you can get in on a zoom together BONUS!
• Friday, May 1st: WK Spirit Day-We may not be at school together but show us all your Falcon Pride by wearing red, black, white, and your WK gear.

post_text:
Further information on the communications distributed today.

W-K is planning on distance learning starting on March 30th as directed by Governor Walz. All communications by the Minnesota Department of Education and the Governor’s office suggest that Distance Learning will START on March 30th. Items needed for distance learning have been put together by the WK staff for distribution. This includes electronic devices, textbooks, other learning materials, the first two weeks of packets as well as other items in student lockers. Students will need these items for distance learning so it is necessary to get these materials in the hands of our families. A pick-up day is one way of distributing these important materials. All staff have worked hard at getting things ready for distribution and it is now time to began that process. How long distance learning will occur is unknown and will be determined by many at the state level.

Thank you and please do not hesitate to contact me at anytime if you have questions.

Jim Freihammer.

post_text:
Attention: Wabasha/Kellogg Families - Meal Delivery Starts Wednesday, March 18th.

If you signed up for meals, yellow busses will be in your neighborhood delivering those meals to the address you shared on the survey.

Meals will be delivered between 11-12 daily. You will receive two meals per child signed up for daily delivery. You will receive a lunch for the day and a breakfast for the following morning. The two meals will be packaged in one bag. We will repeat the process daily.

Please be ready to accept delivery at the entrance to your residence. If you live in an apartment, please be at a doorway that leads directly outside. We need to deliver this meal and give it to a person. We can not just leave it.

Thank you.
